  "title": "Get union of items when using multiple disjunctiveFacetsRefinements",
  "body": "<!--\r\n  Thanks for participating in this project! We will try to answer as soon as possible 🙏\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe 🙏**\r\nOkay... so my case scenario is that I want to get all items (posts) which are either in a particular category or in a particular tag... I thought disjunctive facets would sort the issue for me... but they don't. Only posts that have one of the specified category *AND* one of the specified tags are returned.\r\n\r\n\r\n**Describe the solution you'd like 🤔**\r\nTo solve this, would like union not intersection of all disjunctive facet refinements... i.e. All items that have any of the specified tags `UNION` all of the items that have any of the specified categories.\r\n\r\n**Describe alternatives you've considered ✨**\r\nWell, I have tried disjunctive facets 🙃\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\nTrying to replace WooCommerce' related product algorithm with Algolia instant search using current product's categories/tags.",
